body:
# Slack Bots with Bolt.js

Bolt.js is the official framework for building Slack apps. It handles request verification, event parsing, and OAuth so you can focus on bot logic. See [[slack]] for app creation and authentication.

## Setup

```javascript
import pkg from "@slack/bolt";
const { App } = pkg;

const app = new App({
  token: process.env.SLACK_BOT_TOKEN,
  signingSecret: process.env.SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET,
  socketMode: true,
  appToken: process.env.SLACK_APP_TOKEN
});

(async () => {
  await app.start();
  console.log("Bot is running!");
})();
```

Socket Mode requires an app-level token (`xapp-`). It connects via WebSocket, so no public URL is needed. For HTTP mode, omit `socketMode` and `appToken`, and expose a public endpoint.

## Slash Commands

```javascript
app.command("/hello", async ({ command, ack, respond }) => {
  await ack();
  await respond({
    text: `Hello, <@${command.user_id}>! You said: ${command.text}`
  });
});
```

Register commands in your app settings at https://api.slack.com/apps. The `ack()` call must happen within 3 seconds. Use `respond()` for follow-up messages.

## Events

```javascript
// Listen for messages
app.message("hello", async ({ message, say }) => {
  await say(`Hey there, <@${message.user}>!`);
});

// Listen for app mentions
app.event("app_mention", async ({ event, say }) => {
  await say({
    text: `Thanks for mentioning me, <@${event.user}>!`,
    thread_ts: event.ts  // Reply in thread
  });
});

// Listen for reactions
app.event("reaction_added", async ({ event, say }) => {
  if (event.reaction === "eyes") {
    await say({ text: "I see you looking!", channel: event.item.channel });
  }
});
```

Subscribe to events in your app settings under "Event Subscriptions". See [[slack/events]] for all available event types and subscription setup.

## Interactions

Handle button clicks, menu selections, and modal submissions:

```javascript
// Send a message with a button (see [[slack/block-kit]] for layout)
app.command("/ticket", async ({ command, ack, say }) => {
  await ack();
  await say({
    blocks: [
      {
        type: "section",
        text: { type: "mrkdwn", text: `New ticket from <@${command.user_id}>` },
        accessory: {
          type: "button",
          text: { type: "plain_text", text: "Claim" },
          action_id: "claim_ticket",
          value: command.text
        }
      }
    ],
    text: "New ticket created"
  });
});

// Handle the button click
app.action("claim_ticket", async ({ body, ack, say }) => {
  await ack();
  await say(`<@${body.user.id}> claimed the ticket!`);
});
```

## Modals

```javascript
app.command("/feedback", async ({ command, ack, client }) => {
  await ack();
  await client.views.open({
    trigger_id: command.trigger_id,
    view: {
      type: "modal",
      callback_id: "feedback_modal",
      title: { type: "plain_text", text: "Feedback" },
      submit: { type: "plain_text", text: "Submit" },
      blocks: [
        {
          type: "input",
          block_id: "feedback_input",
          element: { type: "plain_text_input", action_id: "feedback_text", multiline: true },
          label: { type: "plain_text", text: "Your feedback" }
        }
      ]
    }
  });
});

app.view("feedback_modal", async ({ ack, view, body }) => {
  await ack();
  const feedback = view.state.values.feedback_input.feedback_text.value;
  console.log(`Feedback from ${body.user.id}: ${feedback}`);
});
```

See [[slack/block-kit#modals]] for modal layout details and [[slack/block-kit#elements]] for input element types.

## Socket Mode

Socket Mode connects to Slack via WebSocket instead of HTTP. No public URL, firewall rules, or TLS certificate needed. Ideal for development and internal bots.

Enable Socket Mode in app settings, generate an app-level token with `connections:write` scope, and pass it as `appToken` in the App constructor.
